The "System Architect" View
1. Ingestion & Pyramid: * Approach: I used a 25% overlap for the sliding window to ensure context isn't lost at the boundaries. The Knowledge Pyramid reduces "Lost in the Middle" syndrome by allowing the system to query "Distilled Knowledge" (high-level) before diving into "Raw Text" (low-level details).
Decision: I prioritized a "search-down" approach—matching the query against summaries first for speed, then fetching the raw chunk for accuracy.
2. GSM8K Training:
Setup: Used LLaMA 3.2 1B with LoRA. LoRA was chosen because it reduces trainable parameters by >90%, making it possible to train on consumer-grade GPUs (or T4 on Colab) while maintaining high performance.
Metric: Exact Match (EM) is the gold standard for GSM8K, but for this assignment, I focused on a modular training script that handles the padding and truncation logic correctly for autoregressive models.
3. Key Assumptions:
Input documents are text-dense (not heavily reliant on OCR for this version).
Fine-tuning assumes the model already has basic linguistic capabilities and only needs task-specific alignment for mathematical reasoning.
